values:
last night, i became one of the guys.&nbsp;

sam michael and i had a lot of fun trying to play gears of war and listening to the dropkick murphys. it was wonderful.

before that i had a wonderful day with sam and rebecca. we honestly wandered around downtown for hours, taking pictures of beautiful street art and attempting to do some ourselves. sam decided to write "kill all your friends and ride thier corpses like a carousel" on a door. he only wrote about half before we thought someone was coming. we are not ninjas... but it was for the sake of art.&nbsp;

we tried to climb up on top of buildings but failed miserably. honestly, people make it hard for kids to spread good art in this town. i wish there were designated places for kids to share thier words in the form of art. i think it would be wonderful. natalie and i have agreed to do some sort of street art project together. i am hoping with my next coupld of cheques to put away a lot for new york and the rest for new paint and canvas. i want to do art, bitch.

the gallery show i'm in goes up in 6 days and i've never been so excited. i hope that all four of the photos i submitted will be up. and today i am hoping, if i ever get off this blasted computer to go out and start taking more photos. i absolutly love the fact that it's starting to become warm again. last night was freezing, walking around with no coat was dumb. but i'm over it now.

the song i am listening to (colin hay - i just don't think i'll ever get over you) makes me want to cry. the last time i wrote about that song was when i was head over heels for a boy. now i am far from that, but the song still gives me a really warm feeling in my stomach. i just need to be better at this.&nbsp;

well i'm going out to take some photos. right now i am very sore and starting to get butterflies. but i need to go out and take some photos.

love

madison
